        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:27PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 627 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Raymore, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lee's Summit, Grandview, Belton, Raymore, Harrisonville, Pleasant
Hill, Greenwood, Peculiar, Garden City, Lake Winnebago, Lone Jack,
East Lynne, Baldwin Park, Strasburg, Gunn City, and Unity Village.

This includes Interstate 470 between mile markers 4 and 8.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
